**Compile/run**:
     - Compile using
            make 


**Program Purpose**:
     The purpose of this program is to implement string processing and 
     directory traversal utilities. The program reads a file directory using
     an tree to locate all files recursively, and provides string formatting
     to strip non-alphanumeric characters.


**Acknowledgements**: 
     None.


**Files**: 

__processing.cpp__:
     Contains the implementation of the string parsing and directory traversing
     functions. Features `stripNonAlphaNum` to remove trailing/leading 
     non-alphanumeric characters, and `traverseDirectory` to print all file 
     paths recursively.

__processing.h__:
     Contains the definition of the functions for the string parsing and 
     directory traversing functions.

__DirNode.h__:
     Contains the interface for the DirNode class. Represents a folder/node in
     the N-ary file system tree, containing information about subdirectories 
     and files.

__FSTree.h__:
     Contains the interface for the FSTree class. It builds and represents the
     entire file system tree.

__File_Storage.h__:
     Contains the interface for the File_Storage class

__File_Storage.cpp__:
     Contains the implementation of the File_Storage class.

__index.h__:
     Contains the interface for the index class.

__index.cpp__:
     Contains the implementation of the index class.

